goals.question: What is the correlation between u and v?
goals.visualization: scatter plot of u vs v
goals.rationale: This tells us about the relationship between the two variables and whether they are positively, negatively or not correlated.

goals.question: What is the distribution of u?
goals.rationale: This tells us about the spread and skewness of the data in the u column.

goals.question: What is the distribution of v?
goals.rationale: This tells us about the spread and skewness of the data in the v column.

goals.question: What is the joint distribution of u and v?
goals.rationale: This tells us about the relationship between the two variables and how they are distributed together.

goals.question: What is the mean and standard deviation of u and v?
goals.rationale: This gives us a summary of the central tendency and spread of the data in the u and v columns.

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    plt.scatter(data['u'], data['v'])
    plt.title('What is the correlation between u and v?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('u')
    plt.ylabel('v')
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    plt.hist2d(data['u'], data['v'], bins=20)
    plt.title('What is the joint distribution of u and v?', wrap=True)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    plt.hist(data['u'], alpha=0.5, label='u')
    plt.hist(data['v'], alpha=0.5, label='v')
    plt.axvline(data['u'].mean(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label='u mean')
    plt.axvline(data['v'].mean(), color='green', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label='v mean')
    plt.axvline(data['u'].std(), color='blue', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label='u std')
    plt.axvline(data['v'].std(), color='orange', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label='v std')
    plt.legend(loc='upper right')
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    plt.title('What is the mean and standard deviation of u and v?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
